data.text:
This page will be extended as more timetables are found.

All are PDFs unless otherwise stated.

The best location to find out the old timetables for interstate services is in the state-based country rail timetable booklets for each state shown below, as they usually include the full set of interstate trains across Australia at that time, at least until the end of AN.

Also for NSW check State Records as follows:

• NRS 15297, Working timetables 1874-1999

• NRS 15904 Public Timetables 1855-1999

For a comprehensive set of old timetables for Victorian Railways, see Mark Bau’s VR Page.

For 1980s/90s Melbourne “The Met” timetables, check this site by Michael Walker.

Marcus Wong also has some Victorian timetables including Vline and Metro see here.

For South Australian and Commonwealth Railways long distance services over several years, check out Chris Drymalik’s Comrails.com
